# Clone credentials for private-repo plugins declared in sovereign.plugins.json.
#
# Not a real "app" — this directory is never installed on the VPS as a
# runtime .env. It's decrypted only inside the deploy-custom CI job and
# passed straight to the sovereign-runtime build as a BuildKit secret file.
#
# One VAR=value line per plugin repo that needs auth. Each VAR must match
# that plugin's "tokenEnv" field in sovereign.plugins.json exactly. A
# fine-grained GitHub PAT scoped to just that repository with
# Contents: Read-only is the least privilege that works; one PAT can also
# cover several repos under the same owner if you'd rather share one.
#
# Usage:
#   cp apps/_plugin-tokens/.env.example apps/_plugin-tokens/.env
#   nano apps/_plugin-tokens/.env
#   ./scripts/encrypt-env.sh _plugin-tokens
#   git add apps/_plugin-tokens/.env.enc
#   git commit -m "secrets: add plugin-tokens for <plugin>"
#   git push origin main

# ACME_CRM_PLUGIN_TOKEN=ghp_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
